          "page_number": 1,
          "text": "Protocol Number: VALIDATION_PROTOCOL_001\nProtocol Title: A Phase 2 Study of Investigational Product in Adrenal Insufficiency\nBrief Title: PARA OA-012 adrenal study\nSponsor: Example Pharma Inc.\nCRO: Example CRO Services\nPhase 2\nIndication: Adrenal insufficiency\nInvestigational Product: PARA-IP-012 tablets\nStudy Design: Randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled, multi-center\nEnrollment target: 120\nStudy Duration: approximately 24 weeks\n\nInclusion Criteria:\n1. Adults aged 18-75 years with documented adrenal insufficiency.\n2. Able to provide informed consent and comply with visit schedule.\n3. Stable concomitant medications for at least 30 days prior to Day 1.\n\nExclusion Criteria:\n1. Uncontrolled cardiovascular disease.\n2. Pregnancy or breastfeeding.\n3. Prior exposure to PARA-IP-012 within 12 months.\n\nSchedule of Events:\nVisit 1: Screening (window -7 / 0) \u2014 site visit\nVisit 2: Day 1 / Randomization (window -1 / +3) \u2014 site visit\nVisit 3: Day 15 Treatment (window -3 / +3) \u2014 site visit\nVisit 4: Day 39 On-Treatment / Cortisol window (window -3 / +3) \u2014 site visit\nVisit 5: Day 56 Follow-up phone (window -3 / +3) \u2014 phone visit\nVisit 6: Day 84 On-Treatment (window -7 / +7) \u2014 site visit\nVisit 7: Arm A phone monitoring Day 30 (window -2 / +2) \u2014 phone visit Arm A\nVisit 8: Arm B remote monitoring Day 30 (window -2 / +2) \u2014 remote visit Arm B\nVisit 9: End of Study (window -14 / +14) \u2014 site visit\n\nStudy Procedures:\nProcedure: Informed Consent (required)\nProcedure: Vital Signs (required) \u2014 visit: Screening\nProcedure: Hematology / CBC (required)\nProcedure: Clinical Chemistry (required)\nProcedure: Morning Cortisol (required) \u2014 visit: Day 39\nProcedure: IP Administration (required) \u2014 visit: Day 1\nProcedure: AE Assessment (required)\nProcedure: Remote / Phone Contact (required) \u2014 visit: Day 56\nProcedure: ACTH Stimulation Test (conditional) \u2014 if morning cortisol below site threshold\nProcedure: HIT / Platelet Panel (conditional) \u2014 if platelet drop suspected on follow-up\nProcedure: Adrenal insufficiency symptom review (conditional) \u2014 coordinator assessment\n"
        }
